          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Established in 1872, Yellowstone National Park was the world's first national park. Spanning over 2.2 million acres across Wyoming, Montana, and Idaho, it's a living laboratory of geological wonders and diverse ecosystems.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Home to half of the world's geothermal features, including the famous Old Faithful geyser, Yellowstone also hosts the largest high-altitude lake in North America and serves as the core of the Greater Yellowstone Ecosystem.
          </p>
